  MISI-Conference - Special Track on Massive Data Management over Cloud
  (MDMC 2011): http://www.misi-conference.org/

*Vienna**University**of Technology*
*August 22nd to 26th 2011*

The scope of this track will be broad and will encompass diverse aspects 
of massive data computation and management over cloud. Cloud computing 
represents a new paradigm where computing resources storing massive data 
are being offered as services and accessed by others from anywhere in 
the world via Internet. Many facets of massive data computation and 
management issues will need to be revisited in the context of cloud 
computing. Suggested topics for paper submissions include but are not 
limited to:

    * Administration and manageability
    * Large scale Cloud applications
    * Cost Models for Query performance
    * Security and risk in Cloud
    * Fault-tolerance, reliability and consistency models
    * Models for creating and managing federations of clouds and
      internetworking between clouds (InterClouds)
    * Economic models for cloud
    * Cloud Storage for OTLP and OLAP


    Important Dates

Submission of papers: **April 25, 2011
Notification of acceptance: May 25, 2011
Submission of camera-ready papers: June 15, 2011
Conference: August 22 to 26, 2011


    Submission

Submit a full paper of at most 8 pages (IEEE CS formatting guidelines - 
http://www.computer.org/portal/web/cscps/formatting), including figures 
and references. The contact author must provide the following 
information to the workshop chairs: paper title, authors' names, 
affiliations, postal address, phone, fax, and e-mail address of the 
author(s), about 200-250 word abstract, and about five keywords. Prepare 
your paper in PDF file and submit it to the workshop organizers 
(http://stdev.ifs.tuwien.ac.at/misi2011/).
Submission of a paper implies that should the paper be accepted, at 
least one of the authors will register and present the paper in the 
conference. Submissions will be reviewed by at least 3 PC members. 
Accepted papers will be given guidelines in preparing and submitting the 
final manuscript(s) together with the notification of acceptance. 
Authors of selected papers from the track will be invited to submit an 
extended version of their paper to a special issue of a top-quality 
international journal.


    Special Track Chairs

Ladjel Bellatreche, LISI/ENSMA, France


    Program Committee

Reza Akbarinia, INRIA, France

Djamal Benslimane, University Claude Bernard, Lyon, France

Sandro Bimonte, CEMAGREF, France

Alain Crolotte, Teradata USA

Laurent d'Orazio, LIMOS, France

Petro Furtado, University of Coimbra <http://www.dei.uc.pt/>, Portugal

Ahmad Ghazal, Teradata, USA.

David Taniar, Monash University, Australia

...

